      <byline class="print_byline">By Jo Napolitano (NYT)</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Napolitano, Jo</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Burning a church could become hate crime under proposal given initial Missouri House approval (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Burning a church could become a hate crime under a proposal given initial House approval on Monday. The bill, which still awaits final approval, would expand the state's list of hate crimes, which is currently limited to acts against people. It would also stiffen the penalties for those found guilty of such crimes. Under the proposal, anyone convicted of first-  or second-degree arson could face 15 years in prison if it was proved that a place of worship was burned for reasons like race, religion or sexual orientation.</p>
        <p>Jo Napolitano (NYT)</p>
      </block>
